</b> ‘descendant of <i>Ciarán</i>’, a byname from a diminutive of <i>ciar</i> ‘dark, black-haired’. Variants <i>Ó Cearáin</i> and <i>Ó Céirín</i> exist in Irish, see also   Kearns  . The personal name <i>Ciarán</i> was borne by two Irish saints, a hermit of the 5th century and the founder of the monastery at Clonmacnoise (died 547)."]}]},{"name":"Duncan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Donnchadh , also used among people without Scottish connections. This was the name of a 7th-century Scottish saint (abbot of Iona) and two medieval kings of Scotland. The final ‐<i>n</i> in the Anglicized form seems to be the result of confusion with the Gaelic word <i>ceann</i> ‘head’ in the Latinized form <i>Duncanus</i>.  Compare Irish  Donagh ."],"variants":[{"name":"Donnchadh","meanings":["Gaelic: compound of Old Celtic <i>donn</i> ‘brown’ + <i>chadh</i> ‘chief’ or ‘noble’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Duncan Cairns of that Ilk was born in 1336, in Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland. He had at least 1 daughter with Ann Seaver. He died in 1390, in Scotland, at the age of 54."},"et":{"1336–1390":"1336–1390","1336–Female":"1336–Surnud","1355–Female":"1355–Surnud","1336":"1336","Abt 1355":"umbes 1355","1355":"1355","1390":"1390","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland":"Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Edinburgh, Midlothian, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"1336–1390":"1336–1390","1336–Female":"1336–Kuollut","1355–Female":"1355–Kuollut","1336":"1336","Abt 1355":"noin 1355","1355":"1355","1390":"1390","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland":"Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Edinburgh, Midlothian, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"1336–1390":"1336–1390","1336–Female":"1336–Décédée","1355–Female":"1355–Décédée","1336":"1336","Abt 135